==> to pass an array as a parameter with just the values, we cant do as we please, instead we have to

    ==> new int[] {....}

==> instead of using this, we can use variable arguments here, to do the same job  
                        {passing an array as a parameter}


==> a simple method accepting variable argument

void print(int... values)
{
    . . . . 
     . . . .
    . . . . 
     . . . . 
}

==> this will take in the parameters as an array

eg:
    void print(int... values)
    {
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(values));
    }

    int sum(int... values)
    {
        int s;
        for(int i:values)
        {
            s+=i;
        }
        return s;
    }
